Christina and Alex, two lifelong friends, grew up in the same hometown in New York. While Christina says she, “always knew Alex was the one,” it wasn’t until college that their love story truly began. 👩‍❤️‍👨 The bride remembers, “We had just come home from winter break and planned to go on a date. This is your sign not to worry about rain on your wedding day! 🌧️"The weather changed 100 times throughout our wedding day. It went from cold and rainy, to abundant sunshine, and then back to torrential rain," recalls #Kleinfeld bride @angela_licciardello. 🌦️ "We embraced the rain under an overhang for some stunning umbrella shots and I'm so glad we did! ☂️The day was perfect and I wouldn't change a thing - including the weather!" 🥰
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Angela's advice for brides-to-be? 💡"If rain is in the forecast, ask your hair and makeup team if they’re able to stay with you until the ceremony! 💍 This gave me the confidence to run outside and not worry about the weather ruining my hair or makeup!" 💄

This couple said, "See you later, alligator!" to single life as they married in the same place where they fell in love just 8 years earlier. 🐊"Charles and I met in college at the #UniversityOfFlorida," recalls @sorevawaslike. "We were both covering the Florida gymnastics team...me for the school radio station and him for the newspaper.” 📻📰
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Sports had played a special role in the couple's relationship, so it was only fitting that they weaved it into the fabric of their wedding day. 🏈 From a first look inside the university’s football stadium to walking down the aisle surrounded by blue and orange pom poms, Reva and Charles included fun "I Do" details (think custom Jordans and a Gator cake 👟) inspired by their alma mater. 🧡💍
